cabulary":{"typeName":"keywordVocabulary","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"thesaurus"}},{"keywordValue":{"typeName":"keywordValue","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"worship"},"keywordVocabulary":{"typeName":"keywordVocabulary","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"thesaurus"}},{"keywordValue":{"typeName":"keywordValue","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"young adults"},"keywordVocabulary":{"typeName":"keywordVocabulary","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"thesaurus"}},{"keywordValue":{"typeName":"keywordValue","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"youths"},"keywordVocabulary":{"typeName":"keywordVocabulary","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"thesaurus"}}]},{"typeName":"topicClassification","multiple":true,"typeClass":"compound","value":[{"topicClassValue":{"typeName":"topicClassValue","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"ICPSR XVII.B. Social Institutions and Behavior, Religion"},"topicClassVocab":{"typeName":"topicClassVocab","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"ICPSR subject classifications"}}]},{"typeName":"notesText","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"Version Date: 2009-11-17Version Text: 2009-11-17Version Date: 2009-11-17Version Text: 2009-11-17 Subject: null  Type: null  Notes: NCS Wave I data (1998) and Wave II data (2006-07) have been combined into the current version of the cumulative file.  Also, a panel dataset was added, and several sets of Wave I open-ended responses for social service programs, congregational groups, and other items were recoded by the data producer to ensure comparability between Wave I and Wave II.; Subject: null  Type: null  Notes: LRECL with SPSS export file and SAS and SPSS setup files;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: In Wave II a panel component was added to the NCS. In addition to the new cross-section of congregations generated in conjunction with the 2006 GSS, a stratified random sample of congregations who participated in NCS Wave I was drawn.;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: Several sets of Wave I open-ended responses for social service programs, congregational groups, and other items were recoded by the data producer to ensure comparability between Wave I and Wave II.;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: NCS Wave II data collection differed from NCS Wave I data collection in that the NCS Wave II questionnaire was translated into Spanish and eleven interviews were conducted in Spanish.;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: More summertime interviews were conducted in Wave II: 34 percent compared with 20 percent in Wave I. Analysts should ensure that differences between the two waves do not reflect a higher percentage of summer interviews in Wave II.;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: A different data collection strategy produced more in-person interviews in Wave II: 22.5 percent versus 7.5 percent in Wave I. In Wave I, all NCS cases were allocated immediately to field staff around the country who were relatively close to their assigned congregations. In Wave II, data collection began from phone banks in Chicago and Arizona.;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: There are two variables in the panel dataset that are not included in the cumulative cross-sectional dataset: PANEL_ID and PANEL_98.; Subject: null  Type: null  Notes: Stata system file(s), sav Data file(s), stc Data file(s), tsv Data file(s), Data file(s), and electronic documentation.;"},{"typeName":"grantNumber","multiple":true,"typeClass":"compound","value":[{"grantNumberValue":{"typeName":"grantNumberValue","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"#1997-1429-000, #2006-1675-000"}},{"grantNumberValue":{"typeName":"grantNumberValue","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"#9801-020"}},{"grantNumberValue":{"typeName":"grantNumberValue","multiple":false,"typeClass":"primitive","value":"#97-0074, #2005105"}},{"grantNumberValue":{"typeName":"grantN